HEADWORD: Pregustant
<hw>Pre*gus"tant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praegustans</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>praegustare</ets> to taste
beforehand; <ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>gustare</ets> to taste.]</ety>
<def>Tasting beforehand; having a foretaste.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Ed. Rev.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

